padding=\"4\" rowspan=\"2\" background: #f6e39c;\n!Wins\n!Show\n|-\n|4\n|''[[Love, Death & Robots]]''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2\n|''[[Carmen Sandiego (TV series)|Carmen Sandiego]]''\n|-\n|''[[Mickey Mouse (TV series)|Mickey Mouse]]''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://annieawards.org/nominees/ Complete list of 47th Annual Annie Awards nominees]\n{{AnnieAwards}}\n\n[[Category:Annie Awards ceremonies|2019]]\n[[Category:2019 film awards|Annie]]\n[[Category:2020 in Los Angeles|Annie]]\n[[Category:2020 awards in the United States|Annie]]\n", "name_user": "Dronedirt", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eIndividual achievement categories:Typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/47th_Annie_Awards"}
{"title_page": "Al-An'am", "text_new": "{{Infobox Sura\n|Name_of_Surah=Al-\u02beAn\u02bf\u0101m\n|Arabic_name={{lang|ar|\u0671\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0645}}\n|Screenshot_of_Surah=\n|Caption=\n|Classification=[[Makkan sura|Makkan]]\n|Meaning_of_the_name=The Cattle\n|Other_names=Livestock\n|Time_of_revelation=\n|Sura_number=6\n|Number_of_verses=165\n|Juz'_number=7 to 8\n|Hizb_number=13 to 15\n|Number_of_Rukus=20\n|Number_of_sajdahs=none\n|Number_of_words=\n|Number_of_letters=\n|Harf-e-Mukatta'at=\n|Subjectwise_ayat=\n|Previous_Sura=[[Al-Ma'idah]]\n|Next_Sura=[[Al-A'raf]]\n|sound = \n|sound_title = \n}}\n\n{{Quran}}\n\n'''Al-An'am''' ({{lang-ar|\u0671\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0645}} ''{{transl|ar|al-\u02beAn\u02bf\u0101m}}'', \"The Cattle\")<ref name=\"Quran 4 U\">{{cite web|url=http://www.quran4u.com/Tafsir%20Ibn%20Kathir/006%20An%27am.htm  |title=Tafsir Ibn Kathir (English): Surah Al An'am |work=Quran 4 U|author= [[Ibn Kathir]]|accessdate=21 December 2019}}</ref> is the [[List of chapters in the Quran|sixth chapter]] ([[s\u016brah]]) of the [[Qur'an]], with 165 verses ([[\u0101y\u0101t]]). Coming in order in the Qur'an after [[al-Baqarah]], [[Al Imran|Al 'Imran]], [[An-Nisa, 34|an-Nisa']], and [[al-Ma'idah]], all of which were revealed in Madinah, this surah dwells on such themes as rejecting polytheism and unbelief, the establishment of [[Tawhid]] (pure monotheism), the Revelation, Messengership, and Resurrection. Regarding the timing and contextual background of the revelation (''[[Asb\u0101b al-nuz\u016bl]]''), it is a [[Meccan surah|\"Meccan surah]],\" as it is believed to have been revealed in its entirety during the final year of the Makkan period of Islam<ref>{{Cite book|last=\u00dcnal, Ali.|first=|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/234244740|title=The Qur\u02bcan with annotated interpretation in modern English|date=2008|publisher=Tughra Books|year=|isbn=978-1-59784-144-3|location=Somerset, N.J.|pages=267|oclc=234244740}}</ref>. The surah also reports the story of the prophet [[Abraham]]<ref>{{cite quran|6|74|end=80}}</ref>, who calls others to stop worshiping celestial bodies and turns towards God.\n\n==Interpretation==\n{{More citations needed|date=December 2019}}\n===Verse 6:32===\n{{cite quran|6|32|style=nosup|expand=no}} - warns against [[hedonism]]:\n:\"What is the life of this world but play and amusement? But best is the home in the [[Akhirah|hereafter]], for those who are righteous.\"\n\n===Verse 6.59===\n{{cite quran|6|59|style=nosup|expand=no}} - teaches that none but Allah is [[Omniscience|Omniscient]]:\n:\"And with Him are the keys of the Invisible. None but He Knoweth them. And He Knoweth what is in the land and the sea. Not a leaf falleth but He knoweth it, not a grain amid the darkness of the earth, naught of wet or dry but (it is noted) in a clear record.\"\n\n===Verse 6:68===\n{{cite quran|6|68|style=nosup|expand=no}} - commands avoiding talking to disbelievers about revelation:\n:\"And when thou seest those who meddle with Our revelations, withdraw from them until they meddle with another topic. And if the devil causes thee to forget, sit not, after the remembrance, with the congregation of wrong-doers.\"\n\n===Verse 6:73===\n{{cite quran|6|73|style=nosup|expand=no}} - teaches about Allah's [[Omnipotence]]:\n:\"In the day when He Saith: Be! it is.\"\n\n=== Verse 6:78 ===\n<blockquote>Then, when he beheld the sun rising in all its splendor, he said; \"This is my Lord, (is it)? This one is the greatest of all!\" But when it set, he said: \"O my people! Surely I am free from your association of partner with God and from whatever you associate with Him as partners.\" <sup>6:78</sup><ref>{{Cite book|last=\u00dcnal, Ali.|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/234244740|title=The Qur\u02bcan with annotated interpretation in modern English|date=2008|publisher=Tughra Books|isbn=978-1-59784-144-3|location=Somerset, N.J.|oclc=234244740}}</ref></blockquote>This verse hints at an important reality through a grammatical rule which is impossible to render in translation according to Unal: The sun is a feminine word in Arabic; whereas prophet Abraham, used a masculine pronoun when pointing to it.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|last=\u00dcnal, Ali.|first=|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/234244740|title=The Qur\u02bcan with annotated interpretation in modern English|date=2008|publisher=Tughra Books|year=|isbn=978-1-59784-144-3|location=Somerset, N.J.|pages=290|oclc=234244740}}</ref> This means that his people, like almost all other polytheist peoples, considered their greatest deity as being male. As pointed to in note 26 of his interpretation of 4:117, Unal states that \"Whatever they may claim, in nearly all communities that reject Divine Religion in the establishment of their society, women are only objects exploited by men for their interest and tools used to satisfy their carnal desires. Men hold the sovereignty. This is because those reject God's authority depend on and adore force and might; this is possessed and represented by men, rather than women. Therefore a (supreme) god, in such a system, cannot be seen as being female.\"<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n===Verse 6:127===\n{{See also|Divisions of the world in Islam}}\nThe \"abode of peace\"  is also known as Dar al-Islam, or house/abode of Submission.<ref name = \"Quran 4 U\"/> The term also appears in Quran [[Yunus (surah)]] 10.25 as a name of Paradise.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia |encyclopedia=[[The Encyclopaedia of Islam]] |publisher=[[Brill (publisher)|Brill]] |location=Leiden |volume=2 |page=128 |first=T. W. |last=Arnold |author-link=T. W. Arnold |url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.529972/page/n137 |title=Gagauzes - Gakhar |year=1927}}</ref>\n\n===Verses 6:151 - 6:152===\n{{cite quran|6|151|style=nosup|expand=no}} - Mildly resembles parts of The [[Ten Commandments]].<ref>[[Ibn Kathir]], [https://books.google.com/books?id=_053Peu7XSgC&pg=PA237 Stories of the Prophets, From Adam to Muhammad, Ibn Katheer], \"Ibn Katheer states that many of the early Muslim scholars and others maintain that the content of these Ten Commandments exists in the following two Qur'anic verses: \"Say; 'Come, I will rehearse what Allah hath (really) prohibited you from join not anything as equal as Him: be good to your parents; kill not your children on a plea of want - We provide sustenance for you and for them- come not nigh to shameful deeds, whether open or secret; take not life, which Allah hath made sacred, except by way of justice and law: thus doth He command you, that ye may learn wisdom. And come not nigh to the orphan's property, except to improve it, until he attains the age of full strength; give measure and weight with (full) justice; no burden do We place on any soul but that which it can bear - whenever ye speak, speak justly, even if a near relative is concerned; and fulfill the Covenant of Allah thus doth He command you, the ye may remember.\" ( al-An\u02bb\u0101m: 151-2)\"</ref>\n\n{{quote|Say: \"Come, I will recite what your Lord has prohibited you from: \n\u00b7 Join not anything in worship with Him;\n\u00b7 be kind and dutiful to your parents;\n\u00b7 kill not your children because of poverty -- We provide sustenance for you and for them.\n\u00b7 Come not near to Al-Fawahish (immoral sins) whether committed openly or secretly;\n\u00b7 and kill not anyone whom Allah has forbidden, except for a just cause.\nThis He has commanded you that you may understand.\"<ref name = \"Quran 4 U\"/>{{rp|6:151-152}}}}\n\n===Verse 6:159===\nVerse (6:159) is known for forbidding sects and denominations.\n: \"As for those who divide their religion and break up into sects, thou hast no part in them in the least: their affair is with Allah: He will, in the end, tell them the truth of all that they did.\"<ref name = \"Quran 4 U\"/>{{rp|6:159}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n{{Sura|6|[[Al-Ma'ida]]|[[Al-A'raf]]}}\n\n[[Category:Chapters in the Quran|An'am]]\n[[Category:Qur'an articles needing attention]]\n\n\n{{Quran-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Sura\n|Name_of_Surah=Al-\u02beAn\u02bf\u0101m\n|Arabic_name={{lang|ar|\u0671\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0645}}\n|Screenshot_of_Surah=\n|Caption=\n|Classification=[[Makkan sura|Makkan]]\n|Meaning_of_the_name=The Cattle\n|Other_names=Livestock\n|Time_of_revelation=\n|Sura_number=6\n|Number_of_verses=165\n|Juz'_number=7 to 8\n|Hizb_number=13 to 15\n|Number_of_Rukus=20\n|Number_of_sajdahs=none\n|Number_of_words=\n|Number_of_letters=\n|Harf-e-Mukatta'at=\n|Subjectwise_ayat=\n|Previous_Sura=[[Al-Ma'idah]]\n|Next_Sura=[[Al-A'raf]]\n|sound = \n|sound_title = \n}}\n\n{{Quran}}\n\n'''Al-An'am''' ({{lang-ar|\u0671\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0645}} ''{{transl|ar|al-\u02beAn\u02bf\u0101m}}'', \"The Cattle\")<ref name=\"Quran 4 U\">{{cite web|url=http://www.quran4u.com/Tafsir%20Ibn%20Kathir/006%20An%27am.htm  |title=Tafsir Ibn Kathir (English): Surah Al An'am |work=Quran 4 U|author= [[Ibn Kathir]]|accessdate=21 December 2019}}</ref> is the [[List of chapters in the Quran|sixth chapter]] ([[s\u016brah]]) of the [[Qur'an]], with 165 verses ([[\u0101y\u0101t]]). Coming in order in the Qur'an after [[al-Baqarah]], [[Al Imran|Al 'Imran]], [[An-Nisa, 34|an-Nisa']], and [[al-Ma'idah]], all of which were revealed in Madinah, this surah dwells on such themes as rejecting polytheism and unbelief, the establishment of [[Tawhid]] (pure monotheism), the Revelation, Messengership, and Resurrection. Regarding the timing and contextual background of the revelation (''[[Asb\u0101b al-nuz\u016bl]]''), it is a [[Meccan surah|\"Meccan surah]],\" as it is believed to have been revealed in its entirety during the final year of the Makkan period of Islam<ref>{{Cite book|last=\u00dcnal, Ali.|first=|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/234244740|title=The Qur\u02bcan with annotated interpretation in modern English|date=2008|publisher=Tughra Books|year=|isbn=978-1-59784-144-3|location=Somerset, N.J.|pages=267|oclc=234244740}}</ref>. The surah also reports the story of the prophet [[Abraham]]<ref>{{cite quran|6|74|end=80}}</ref>, who calls others to stop worshiping celestial bodies and turns towards Allah.\n\n==Interpretation==\n{{More citations needed|date=December 2019}}\n===Verse 6:32===\n{{cite quran|6|32|style=nosup|expand=no}} - warns against [[hedonism]]:\n:\"What is the life of this world but play and amusement? But best is the home in the [[Akhirah|hereafter]], for those who are righteous.\"\n\n===Verse 6.59===\n{{cite quran|6|59|style=nosup|expand=no}} - teaches that none but Allah is [[Omniscience|Omniscient]]:\n:\"And with Him are the keys of the Invisible. None but He Knoweth them. And He Knoweth what is in the land and the sea. Not a leaf falleth but He knoweth it, not a grain amid the darkness of the earth, naught of wet or dry but (it is noted) in a clear record.\"\n\n===Verse 6:68===\n{{cite quran|6|68|style=nosup|expand=no}} - commands avoiding talking to disbelievers about revelation:\n:\"And when thou seest those who meddle with Our revelations, withdraw from them until they meddle with another topic. And if the devil causes thee to forget, sit not, after the remembrance, with the congregation of wrong-doers.\"\n\n===Verse 6:73===\n{{cite quran|6|73|style=nosup|expand=no}} - teaches about Allah's [[Omnipotence]]:\n:\"In the day when He Saith: Be! it is.\"\n\n=== Verse 6:78 ===\n<blockquote>Then, when he beheld the sun rising in all its splendor, he said; \"This is my Lord, (is it)? This one is the greatest of all!\" But when it set, he said: \"O my people! Surely I am free from your association of partner with God and from whatever you associate with Him as partners.\" <sup>6:78</sup><ref>{{Cite book|last=\u00dcnal, Ali.|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/234244740|title=The Qur\u02bcan with annotated interpretation in modern English|date=2008|publisher=Tughra Books|isbn=978-1-59784-144-3|location=Somerset, N.J.|oclc=234244740}}</ref></blockquote>This verse hints at an important reality through a grammatical rule which is impossible to render in translation according to Unal: The sun is a feminine word in Arabic; whereas the Prophet Abraham, used a masculine pronoun when pointing to it.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|last=\u00dcnal, Ali.|first=|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/234244740|title=The Qur\u02bcan with annotated interpretation in modern English|date=2008|publisher=Tughra Books|year=|isbn=978-1-59784-144-3|location=Somerset, N.J.|pages=290|oclc=234244740}}</ref> This means that his people, like almost all other polytheist peoples, considered their greatest deity as being male. As pointed to in note 26 of his interpretation of 4:117, Unal states that \"Whatever they may claim, in nearly all communities that reject Divine Religion in the establishment of their society, women are only objects exploited by men for their interest and tools used to satisfy their carnal desires. Men hold the sovereignty. This is because those reject God's authority depend on and adore force and might; this is possessed and represented by men, rather than women. Therefore a (supreme) god, in such a system, cannot be seen as being female.\"<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n===Verse 6:127===\n{{See also|Divisions of the world in Islam}}\nThe \"abode of peace\"  is also known as Dar al-Islam, or house/abode of Submission.<ref name = \"Quran 4 U\"/> The term also appears in Quran [[Yunus (surah)]] 10.25 as a name of Paradise.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia |encyclopedia=[[The Encyclopaedia of Islam]] |publisher=[[Brill (publisher)|Brill]] |location=Leiden |volume=2 |page=128 |first=T. W. |last=Arnold |author-link=T. W. Arnold |url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.529972/page/n137 |title=Gagauzes - Gakhar |year=1927}}</ref>\n\n===Verses 6:151 - 6:152===\n{{cite quran|6|151|style=nosup|expand=no}} - Mildly resembles parts of The [[Ten Commandments]].<ref>[[Ibn Kathir]], [https://books.google.com/books?id=_053Peu7XSgC&pg=PA237 Stories of the Prophets, From Adam to Muhammad, Ibn Katheer], \"Ibn Katheer states that many of the early Muslim scholars and others maintain that the content of these Ten Commandments exists in the following two Qur'anic verses: \"Say; 'Come, I will rehearse what Allah hath (really) prohibited you from join not anything as equal as Him: be good to your parents; kill not your children on a plea of want - We provide sustenance for you and for them- come not nigh to shameful deeds, whether open or secret; take not life, which Allah hath made sacred, except by way of justice and law: thus doth He command you, that ye may learn wisdom. And come not nigh to the orphan's property, except to improve it, until he attains the age of full strength; give measure and weight with (full) justice; no burden do We place on any soul but that which it can bear - whenever ye speak, speak justly, even if a near relative is concerned; and fulfill the Covenant of Allah thus doth He command you, the ye may remember.\" ( al-An\u02bb\u0101m: 151-2)\"</ref>\n\n{{quote|Say: \"Come, I will recite what your Lord has prohibited you from: \n\u00b7 Join not anything in worship with Him;\n\u00b7 be kind and dutiful to your parents;\n\u00b7 kill not your children because of poverty -- We provide sustenance for you and for them.\n\u00b7 Come not near to Al-Fawahish (immoral sins) whether committed openly or secretly;\n\u00b7 and kill not anyone whom Allah has forbidden, except for a just cause.\nThis He has commanded you that you may understand.\"<ref name = \"Quran 4 U\"/>{{rp|6:151-152}}}}\n\n===Verse 6:159===\nVerse (6:159) is known for forbidding sects and denominations.\n: \"As for those who divide their religion and break up into sects, thou hast no part in them in the least: their affair is with Allah: He will, in the end, tell them the truth of all that they did.\"<ref name = \"Quran 4 U\"/>{{rp|6:159}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n{{Sura|6|[[Al-Ma'ida]]|[[Al-A'raf]]}}\n\n[[Category:Chapters in the Quran|An'am]]\n[[Category:Qur'an articles needing attention]]\n\n\n{{Quran-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ariadenus", "label": "safe", "comment": "removed honorifics.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al-An%27am"}
{"title_page": "Lives & Livelihoods Fund", "text_new": "{{External links|date=June 2019}}\nThe [https://www.isdb.org/partnership/lives-and-livelihoods-fund Lives & Livelihoods Fund]   ({{lang-ar| \u0635\u0646\u062f\u0648\u0642 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u064a\u0634 \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0639\u064a\u0634\u0629}}) (LLF) is a [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KDN5T3G8fH4 $2.5 billion multilateral development initiative] created by the [https://www.arabianbusiness.com/gates-agrees-contribute-muslim-development-projects-669360.html Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation], the [[Islamic Development Bank]] [http://www.arabnews.com/node/991806/middleeast](IsDB) [http://saudigazette.com.sa/article/520398/Life/Health/Innovation-and-partnership-to-tackle-poverty], the [[Kingdom of Saudi Arabia]], the [[United Arab Emirates]], the [http://philanthropynewsdigest.org/news/qatar-commits-50-million-to-gates-foundation-idb-s-anti-poverty-fund State of Qatar], and most recently the UK's Department for International Development (December 2020). According to Gulf News, the five year fund is the \"largest ever Middle-East based, fully-multilateral development initiative\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://gulfnews.com/news/gulf/saudi-arabia/bill-gates-teams-up-with-gulf-states-to-fight-poverty-1.1909264|title=Bill Gates teams up with Gulf states to fight poverty|website=Gulf News|access-date=2017-08-07}}</ref> In 2015 ''[[The Economist]]'' reported on the fund creation for tackling poverty and ill health in the Muslim world, and that the IsDB and BMGF sought to collaborate in the fund with Gulf countries.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.economist.com/news/finance-and-economics/21679824-western-and-middle-eastern-donors-pool-cash-and-expertise-two-pronged-attack|title=Bill Gates and the IDB - Two-pronged attack: Western and Middle Eastern donors pool cash and expertise|website=The Economist|access-date=2017-08-07}}</ref> The fund started its operations in September 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.arabnews.com/node/991806/middleeast#photo/1|title=Bill Gates-inspired anti-poverty initiative takes shape in Jeddah|website=Arab News|access-date=2017-08-07}}</ref> [http://www.linkedin.com/pub/dir/dr.%20waleed/addas Dr. Waleed Addas] is the Head of the Lives and Livelihoods [https://english.alarabiya.net/en/views/news/middle-east/2017/05/22/A-development-solution-from-the-Muslim-world.html Fund], Islamic Development Bank.\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Governance and Stakeholders.jpg|alt=|thumb|Governance and Stakeholders]] -->\n\n===[https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/2018-10/LLF%20English%20Guide.pdf Financing Model]===\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:LLF Financing Model.jpg|thumb|Financing Model of the LLF]] -->\nThe LLF is a collaboration between the IsDB and Donor partners<ref>Donor Partners include the [https://www.adfd.ae/english/pages/home.aspx Abu Dhabi Fund for Development (ADFD)], [https://www.gatesfoundation.org/ Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation (BMGF)], [https://isfd.isdb.org/EN/Pages/default.aspx Islamic Solidarity Fund for Development (ISFD)]. [https://www.ksrelief.org/English/pages/home.aspx King Salman Humanitarian Aid and Relief Center (KSRelief)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502115252/https://www.ksrelief.org/English/Pages/Home.aspx |date=2019-05-02 }}, the [http://www.qatarfund.org.qa Qatar Fund for Development (QFFD)], and most recently the UK Department for International Development (DFID).</ref> bringing an innovative financing solution for 33 of the member [https://www.isdb.org/isdb-member-countries countries] of the Bank.  \n\nDonor grants are blended with ordinary capital resources (OCR) to provide concessional financing for IsDB member countries.  For projects in the least developed member countries (LDMCs), LLF offers ~35% grant portions and 65% IsDB OCR financing (indivisible). The International Monetary Fund rules allow lower middle-income countries (LMICs) to borrow at market rates, the Lives and Livelihoods Fund offers packages of 10% grant portion and 90% ordinary financing, which makes loans significantly cheaper for the recipient countries. \n\nThe blending results in substantially more funds, at concessional rates, made available for social development projects in geographies where they are most needed. The concessionality is leveraged to target key drivers of poverty in the beneficiary countries.\n\n===[https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/2018-10/LLF%20English%20Guide.pdf Targeting the most vulnerable]===\nThe Fund targets investments towards key drivers of poverty in the most marginalized groups. Projects are finances in health, agriculture, and basic infrastructure sectors in member countries. Health projects focus on primary healthcare system strengthening, and control/elimination of infectious diseases. Agriculture projects are geared towards increasing the productivity of small-holder farmers. Basic infrastructure investments support projects such as generating and distributing off-grid rural power, installing small-scale water and sanitation schemes, and setting up mobile communications for digital payments. \n\n===[https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/2018-10/LLF%20English%20Guide.pdf Countries Eligible for LLF Financing]===\nThe Lives and Livelihoods Fund enables the least developed member countries of the Islamic Development Bank to finance projects that will help lift millions out of poverty. \n[[File:Countries eligible for LLF financing.jpg|thumb]]<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Eligible Countries for LLF Financing.jpg|thumb|Member countries eligible for LLF Financing|alt=]] -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+''Countries Eligible for LLF Financing''\n|Afghanistan\n|Burkina Faso\n|Comoros\n|'''Egypt*'''\n|Guinea Bissau\n|Maldives\n|'''Morocco*'''\n|'''Nigeria*'''\n|Senegal\n|Sudan\n|Uganda\n|-\n|Bangladesh\n|Cameroon\n|Cote d' Ivoire\n|The Gambia\n|'''Indonesia*'''\n|Mali\n|Mozambique\n|Pakistan\n|Sierra Leone\n|Tajikistan\n|'''Uzbekistan*'''\n|-\n|Benin\n|Chad\n|Djibouti\n|Guinea\n|Kyrgyz Republic\n|Mauritania\n|Niger\n|Palestine\n|Somalia\n|Togo\n|Yemen\n|}\n'''''<sup>*(Countries in BOLD) Eligible for 10% grant vs 35% for others.</sup>'''''\n\n===[https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/2018-10/LLF%20English%20Guide.pdf Financing Domains and allocations]===\n'''Health''' projects are allotted 20-60% of the total LLF funding. Health projects which are eligible for LLF financing focus on:\n\n* Combating infectious diseases like malaria\n* HIV/AIDS, polio and neglected tropical diseases\n* Ensuring routine immunization coverage\n* Strengthening primary healthcare systems for equitable access to quality healthcare services. \n\n'''Agriculture''' projects are allotted 20-60% of the total LLF funding. Agriculture projects which are eligible for LLF financing focus on:\n\n* Boosting production of staple crops and livestock by smallholder farmers and pastoralists \u2013 those who produce 80% of food in key regions\n* Providing smallholder farmers and producers with better access to markets and technology\n* Increasing women's empowerment in agriculture\n* Increasing access to, and consumption of, a nutritious diet\n* Increasing income stability among smallholder farmers, including through favoring entrepreneurship.\n\n'''Basic Infrastructure''' projects will be allotted a maximum of 20% of the total LLF funding. The projects which are eligible for LLF financing focus on:\n\n* Providing better access to water and sanitation services\n* Improving access to a reliable electric supply\n* Providing greater access to mobile and digital communications\n* Increasing protection from flooding for individuals, housing and community facilities.\n\n<br />\n\n===[https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/2018-11/2017%20LLF%20Annual%20Report-English.pdf LLF Projects and developmental impact]===\n[[File:Portfolio 2016-19.jpg|thumb]]\nThe LLF Impact Committee have approved [http://www.philanthropyage.org/finance/gcc-backed-fund-signs-32m-malaria-eradication-deal projects] worth over US$1 billion in the first four years (2016-2019)[https://13martyrs.wordpress.com/tag/lives-and-livelihoods-fund/] since the Fund's inception. These projects are spread across Sub-Saharan Africa, MENA, and [https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/2018-11/2017%20LLF%20Annual%20Report-English.pdf Asia].   \n\nThe maiden Annual Reports of the LLF was published in 2017. The following Annual Reports of the Lives and Livelihoods Fund are available to-date: \n\n*[https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/media/documents/2019-01/2017%20LLF%20Annual%20Report-English.pdf Annual Report 2017 - Lives and Livelihoods Fund (LLF)]\n*[https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/media/documents/2019-06/LLF%202018%20Annual%20Report%20%28Eng%29.pdf Annual Report 2018 - Lives and Livelihoods Fund (LLF)]\n\nThe LLF and it's investments in health, agriculture, and basic infrastructure projects are featured in a number of IsDB reports including, but not limited to: \n\n* [https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/media/documents/2018-12/IsDB-Annual%20Report-1437H%282016%29-Digest.pdf Annual Report 2016 (Digest) - Islamic Development Bank]  \n* [https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/media/documents/2018-12/IsDB-Annual%20Report-1438H%282017%29-Digest.pdf Annual Report 2017 (Digest) - Islamic Development Bank] \n* [https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/media/documents/2018-12/Final%20ADER%202017-compressed.pdf Development Effectiveness Report 2017 - Islamic Development Bank] \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\nhttps://english.alarabiya.net/en/views/news/middle-east/2017/05/22/A-development-solution-from-the-Muslim-world.html\nhttp://www.isdb-pilot.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/A-Guide-to-the-Lives-and-Livelihoods-Funds.pdf\n\nhttps://www.isdb.org/partnership/lives-and-livelihoods-fund\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lives and Livelihoods Fund}}\n[[Category:Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 2016]]\n[[Category:International development agencies]]\n[[Category:Multilateral relations]]\n\n\n{{international-org-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{External links|date=June 2019}}\nThe [https://www.isdb.org/partnership/lives-and-livelihoods-fund Lives & Livelihoods Fund]   ({{lang-ar| \u0635\u0646\u062f\u0648\u0642 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u064a\u0634 \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0639\u064a\u0634\u0629}}) (LLF) is a [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KDN5T3G8fH4 $2.5 billion multilateral development initiative] created by the [https://www.arabianbusiness.com/gates-agrees-contribute-muslim-development-projects-669360.html Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation], the [[Islamic Development Bank]] [http://www.arabnews.com/node/991806/middleeast](IsDB) [http://saudigazette.com.sa/article/520398/Life/Health/Innovation-and-partnership-to-tackle-poverty], the [[Kingdom of Saudi Arabia]], the [[United Arab Emirates]], the [http://philanthropynewsdigest.org/news/qatar-commits-50-million-to-gates-foundation-idb-s-anti-poverty-fund State of Qatar], and most recently the UK's Department for International Development (December 2020). According to Gulf News, the five year fund is the \"largest ever Middle-East based, fully-multilateral development initiative\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://gulfnews.com/news/gulf/saudi-arabia/bill-gates-teams-up-with-gulf-states-to-fight-poverty-1.1909264|title=Bill Gates teams up with Gulf states to fight poverty|website=Gulf News|access-date=2017-08-07}}</ref> In 2015 ''[[The Economist]]'' reported on the fund creation for tackling poverty and ill health in the Muslim world, and that the IsDB and BMGF sought to collaborate in the fund with Gulf countries.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.economist.com/news/finance-and-economics/21679824-western-and-middle-eastern-donors-pool-cash-and-expertise-two-pronged-attack|title=Bill Gates and the IDB - Two-pronged attack: Western and Middle Eastern donors pool cash and expertise|website=The Economist|access-date=2017-08-07}}</ref> The fund started its operations in September 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.arabnews.com/node/991806/middleeast#photo/1|title=Bill Gates-inspired anti-poverty initiative takes shape in Jeddah|website=Arab News|access-date=2017-08-07}}</ref> [http://www.linkedin.com/pub/dir/dr.%20waleed/addas Dr. Waleed Addas] is the Head of the Lives and Livelihoods [https://english.alarabiya.net/en/views/news/middle-east/2017/05/22/A-development-solution-from-the-Muslim-world.html Fund], Islamic Development Bank.\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Governance and Stakeholders.jpg|alt=|thumb|Governance and Stakeholders]] -->\n\n===[https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/2018-10/LLF%20English%20Guide.pdf Financing Model]===\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:LLF Financing Model.jpg|thumb|Financing Model of the LLF]] -->\nThe LLF is a collaboration between the IsDB and Donor partners<ref>Donor Partners include the [https://www.adfd.ae/english/pages/home.aspx Abu Dhabi Fund for Development (ADFD)], [https://www.gatesfoundation.org/ Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation (BMGF)], [https://isfd.isdb.org/EN/Pages/default.aspx Islamic Solidarity Fund for Development (ISFD)]. [https://www.ksrelief.org/English/pages/home.aspx King Salman Humanitarian Aid and Relief Center (KSRelief)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502115252/https://www.ksrelief.org/English/Pages/Home.aspx |date=2019-05-02 }}, the [http://www.qatarfund.org.qa Qatar Fund for Development (QFFD)], and most recently the UK Department for International Development (DFID).</ref> bringing an innovative financing solution for 33 of the member [https://www.isdb.org/isdb-member-countries countries] of the Bank.  \n\nDonor grants are blended with ordinary capital resources (OCR) to provide concessional financing for IsDB member countries.  For projects in the least developed member countries (LDMCs), LLF offers ~35% grant portions and 65% IsDB OCR financing (indivisible). The International Monetary Fund rules allow lower middle-income countries (LMICs) to borrow at market rates, the Lives and Livelihoods Fund offers packages of 10% grant portion and 90% ordinary financing, which makes loans significantly cheaper for the recipient countries. \n\nThe blending results in substantially more funds, at concessional rates, made available for social development projects in geographies where they are most needed. The concessionality is leveraged to target key drivers of poverty in the beneficiary countries.\n\n===[https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/2018-10/LLF%20English%20Guide.pdf Targeting the most vulnerable]===\nThe Fund targets investments towards key drivers of poverty in the most marginalized groups. Projects are finances in health, agriculture, and basic infrastructure sectors in member countries. Health projects focus on primary healthcare system strengthening, and control/elimination of infectious diseases. Agriculture projects are geared towards increasing the productivity of small-holder farmers. Basic infrastructure investments support projects such as generating and distributing off-grid rural power, installing small-scale water and sanitation schemes, and setting up mobile communications for digital payments. \n\n===[https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/2018-10/LLF%20English%20Guide.pdf Countries Eligible for LLF Financing]===\nThe Lives and Livelihoods Fund enables the least developed member countries of the Islamic Development Bank to finance projects that will help lift millions out of poverty. \n[[File:Countries eligible for LLF financing.jpg|thumb]]<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Eligible Countries for LLF Financing.jpg|thumb|Member countries eligible for LLF Financing|alt=]] -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+''Countries Eligible for LLF Financing''\n|Afghanistan\n|Burkina Faso\n|Comoros\n|'''Egypt*'''\n|Guinea Bissau\n|Maldives\n|'''Morocco*'''\n|'''Nigeria*'''\n|Senegal\n|Sudan\n|Uganda\n|-\n|Bangladesh\n|Cameroon\n|Cote d' Ivoire\n|The Gambia\n|'''Indonesia*'''\n|Mali\n|Mozambique\n|Pakistan\n|Sierra Leone\n|Tajikistan\n|'''Uzbekistan*'''\n|-\n|Benin\n|Chad\n|Djibouti\n|Guinea\n|Kyrgyz Republic\n|Mauritania\n|Niger\n|Palestine\n|Somalia\n|Togo\n|Yemen\n|}\n'''''<sup>*(Countries in BOLD) Eligible for 10% grant vs 35% for others.</sup>'''''\n\n===[https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/2018-10/LLF%20English%20Guide.pdf Financing Domains and allocations]===\n'''Health''' projects are allotted 20-60% of the total LLF funding. Health projects which are eligible for LLF financing focus on:\n\n* Combating infectious diseases like malaria\n* HIV/AIDS, polio and neglected tropical diseases\n* Ensuring routine immunization coverage\n* Strengthening primary healthcare systems for equitable access to quality healthcare services. \n\n'''Agriculture''' projects are allotted 20-60% of the total LLF funding. Agriculture projects which are eligible for LLF financing focus on:\n\n* Boosting production of staple crops and livestock by smallholder farmers and pastoralists \u2013 those who produce 80% of food in key regions\n* Providing smallholder farmers and producers with better access to markets and technology\n* Increasing women\u2019s empowerment in agriculture\n* Increasing access to, and consumption of, a nutritious diet\n* Increasing income stability among smallholder farmers, including through favoring entrepreneurship.\n\n'''Basic Infrastructure''' projects will be allotted a maximum of 20% of the total LLF funding. The projects which are eligible for LLF financing focus on:\n\n* Providing better access to water and sanitation services\n* Improving access to a reliable electric supply\n* Providing greater access to mobile and digital communications\n* Increasing protection from flooding for individuals, housing and community facilities.\n\n<br />\n\n===[https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/2018-11/2017%20LLF%20Annual%20Report-English.pdf LLF Projects and developmental impact]===\n[[File:Portfolio 2016-19.jpg|thumb]]\nThe LLF Impact Committee have approved [http://www.philanthropyage.org/finance/gcc-backed-fund-signs-32m-malaria-eradication-deal projects] worth over USD 1 billion in the first four years (2016-2019)[https://13martyrs.wordpress.com/tag/lives-and-livelihoods-fund/] since the Fund's inception. These projects are spread across Sub-Saharan Africa, MENA, and [https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/2018-11/2017%20LLF%20Annual%20Report-English.pdf Asia].   \n\nThe maiden Annual Reports of the LLF was published in 2017. The following Annual Reports of the Lives and Livelihoods Fund are available to-date: \n\n*[https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/media/documents/2019-01/2017%20LLF%20Annual%20Report-English.pdf Annual Report 2017 - Lives and Livelihoods Fund (LLF)]\n*[https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/media/documents/2019-06/LLF%202018%20Annual%20Report%20%28Eng%29.pdf Annual Report 2018 - Lives and Livelihoods Fund (LLF)]\n\nThe LLF and it's investments in health, agriculture, and basic infrastructure projects are featured in a number of IsDB reports including, but not limited to: \n\n* [https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/media/documents/2018-12/IsDB-Annual%20Report-1437H%282016%29-Digest.pdf Annual Report 2016 (Digest) - Islamic Development Bank]  \n* [https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/media/documents/2018-12/IsDB-Annual%20Report-1438H%282017%29-Digest.pdf Annual Report 2017 (Digest) - Islamic Development Bank] \n* [https://www.isdb.org/sites/default/files/media/documents/2018-12/Final%20ADER%202017-compressed.pdf Development Effectiveness Report 2017 - Islamic Development Bank] \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\nhttps://english.alarabiya.net/en/views/news/middle-east/2017/05/22/A-development-solution-from-the-Muslim-world.html\nhttp://www.isdb-pilot.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/A-Guide-to-the-Lives-and-Livelihoods-Funds.pdf\n\nhttps://www.isdb.org/partnership/lives-and-livelihoods-fund\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lives and Livelihoods Fund}}\n[[Category:Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 2016]]\n[[Category:International development agencies]]\n[[Category:Multilateral relations]]\n\n\n{{international-org-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: USD  \u2192 US$, \u2019s \u2192 's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lives_%26_Livelihoods_Fund"}
{"title_page": "Madhyapurisvarar Temple, Paranjervazhi", "text_new": "{{short description|Temple in India}}\n'''Madhyapurisvarar Temple, Paranjervazhi''' is a [[Shiva|Siva]] temple in [[Erode]] district in [[Tamil Nadu]] (India).<ref name=\"bmj\">\u0baa\u0bc1.\u0bae\u0bbe.\u0b9c\u0bc6\u0baf\u0b9a\u0bc6\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bcd, \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0bb5\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd, \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd, \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bc8, 2009</ref><ref>[https://shaivam.org/temples-of-lord-shiva/moovar-thevara-vaippu-thalangal \u0baa\u0bb0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbf]</ref><ref>[http://www.shivatemples.com/vt/vtlist3.php \u0baa\u0bb0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbf]</ref>\n\n==Vaippu Sthalam==\nIt is one of the shrines of the [[Vaippu Sthalam]]s sung by Tamil Saivite [[Nayanars|Nayanar]] [[Appar]]. Now, this place is known as Paranjervazhi.<ref name=parappalli>[https://shaivam.org/hindu-hub/temples/place/427/parappalli-mathiyapureeswarar-temple \u0baa\u0bb0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbf (\u0baa\u0bb0\u0b9e\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bb4\u0bbf) Parappalli (Paranjervazhi)]</ref>\n\n==Presiding deity==\nThe presiding deity is Madhyapurisvarar. The Goddess is known as Sukundha Kunthalambikai.<ref name=parappalli/>\n\n==Location==\nThe temple is situated in Paranjervazhi in Kangeyam-Chennimalai road, at a distance of 8&nbsp;km from Natthakadayur.<ref>[http://www.shivatemples.com/vt/vt_kovil3/vt102.php \u0bae\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bc0\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://shaivam.org/hindu-hub/temples/place/427/parappalli-mathiyapureeswarar-temple \u0bae\u0bc2\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0bb5\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd, \u0baa\u0bb0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbf - parappaLLi Sl.No.203]\n* [http://www.shivatemples.com/vt/vtlist3.php \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0bb5\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd, \u0baa\u0bb0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbf Sl.No.102, Appar 6-71-1]\n\n{{Vaippu sthalam}}\n\n{{coord missing|Tamil Nadu}}\n\n[[Category:Shiva temples in Erode district]]\n\n\n{{India-Hindu-temple-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Temple in India}}\n'''Madhyapurisvarar Temple, Paranjervazhi''' is a [[Shiva|Siva]] temple in [[Erode]] district in [[Tamil Nadu]] (India).<ref name=\"bmj\">\u0baa\u0bc1.\u0bae\u0bbe.\u0b9c\u0bc6\u0baf\u0b9a\u0bc6\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bcd, \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0bb5\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd, \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd, \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bc8, 2009</ref><ref>[https://shaivam.org/temples-of-lord-shiva/moovar-thevara-vaippu-thalangal \u0baa\u0bb0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbf]</ref><ref>[http://www.shivatemples.com/vt/vtlist3.php \u0baa\u0bb0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbf]</ref>\n\n==Vaippu Sthalam==\nIt is one of the shrines of the [[Vaippu Sthalam]]s sung by Tamil Saivite [[Nayanars|Nayanar]] [[Appar]]. Now, this place is known as Paranjervazhi.<ref name=parappalli>[https://shaivam.org/hindu-hub/temples/place/427/parappalli-mathiyapureeswarar-temple \u0baa\u0bb0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbf (\u0baa\u0bb0\u0b9e\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bb4\u0bbf) Parappalli (Paranjervazhi)]</ref>\n\n==Presiding deity==\nThe presiding deity is Madhyapurisvarar. The Goddess is known as Sukundha Kunthalambikai.<ref name=parappalli/>\n\n==Location==\nThe temple is situated in Paranjervazhi in Kangeyam-Chennimalai road, at a distance of 8&nbsp;km from Natthakadayur.<ref>[http://www.shivatemples.com/vt/vt_kovil3/vt102.php \u0bae\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bc0\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://shaivam.org/hindu-hub/temples/place/427/parappalli-mathiyapureeswarar-temple \u0bae\u0bc2\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0bb5\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd, \u0baa\u0bb0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbf - parappaLLi Sl.No.203]\n* [http://www.shivatemples.com/vt/vtlist3.php \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0bb5\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd, \u0baa\u0bb0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbf Sl.No.102, Appar 6-71-1]\n\n{{Vaippu sthalam}}\n\n{{coord missing|Tamil Nadu}}\n\n[[Category:Shiva temples in Erode district]]\n\n{{Hindu-temple-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Titodutta", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:stub classify", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madhyapurisvarar_Temple,_Paranjervazhi"}
{"title_page": "87 (number)", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n  {{refimprove |date=April  2016}}\n  {{example farm |date=March 2010}}\n}}\n{{Infobox number\n| number = 87b of. Rd Obudu cR.state\n| divisor = 1, 3, 29, 87\n\n}}\n'''87''' ('''eighty-seven''') is the [[natural number]] following [[86 (number)|86]] and preceding [[88 (number)|88]].\n\n==In mathematics==\n'''87''' is:\n\n* the sum of the squares of the first four primes (87 = 2<sup>2</sup> + 3<sup>2</sup> + 5<sup>2</sup> + 7<sup>2</sup>).\n* the sum of the sums of the divisors of the first 10 [[positive integers]].<ref>{{Cite OEIS|1=A024916|2=sum_{k=1..n} sigma(k) where sigma(n) = sum of divisors of n}}</ref>\n* the twenty-sixth distinct [[semiprime]] and the eighth of the form (3.q).\n* 5! - 4! - 3! - 2! - 1! = 87\n\n==In sports==\n* [[Cricket]] [[Cricket in Australia|in Australia]] holds 87 as a superstitiously unlucky score and is referred to as \"the devil's number.\" This originates from the fact that 87 is [[13 (number)|13]] runs short of a [[Century (cricket)|century]]. 187, 287 and so on are also considered unlucky but is not as common as 87 on its own. \n* In the [[National Hockey League]], [[Wayne Gretzky]] scored a league-high 87 goals with the [[Edmonton Oilers]] in the [[1983\u201384 NHL season]].\n\n==In other fields==\n'''Eighty-seven''' is also:\n\n*The [[atomic number]] of [[francium]]\n*An answer to a popular puzzle question states 16, 06, 68, 88, xx, 98. The answer is 87 when looked upside down.\n*The number of years between the signing of the [[U.S. Declaration of Independence]] and the [[Battle of Gettysburg]], immortalized in [[Abraham Lincoln]]'s [[Gettysburg Address]] with the phrase \"''[[Eighty|fourscore]]'' and seven years ago...\"\n*The model number of [[Junkers Ju 87]]\n*The number of the French department [[Haute-Vienne]]\n*The [[code for international direct dial]] phone calls to [[Inmarsat]] and other services\n*The 87 [[filter (photography)|photographic filter]] blocks visible light allowing only infrared light to pass\n*The [[ISBN]] Group Identifier for books published in Denmark.\n*The opus number of the [[24 Preludes and Fugues (Shostakovich)|24 Preludes and Fugues]] of [[Dmitri Shostakovich]].\n*In [[model railroading]], the ratio of the popular [[H0 scale]] is 1:87. [[Proto:87]] scale claims to offer precise proportions of wheels and tracks of real railroads.\n*[[David Bowie]] CD (1987) ''[[Never Let Me Down]]'' includes the song, \"[['87 and Cry]]\"\n*The [[87th United States Congress]] met from January 3, 1961 - January 3, 1963, during John F. Kennedy's time in office\n*[[Ed McBain]]'s ''[[87th Precinct]]: Lightning'' film starred [[Randy Quaid]] (1995)\n*87 punch includes one bottle of [[Bacardi]] rum (eight years aged) and [[7-up]] (two-liter bottle)\n*[[Wenger]] [[Swiss Army Knife]] version XXL, listed in the ''[[Guinness Book of World Records]]'' as the world's most multi-functional [[penknife]] with 87 tools\n*''[[Sonnet 87]]'' by [[William Shakespeare]]\n*Vault 87 is a main location in the game ''[[Fallout 3]]''\n*[[M87*]] is the first black hole ever photographed.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of highways numbered 87]]\n{{Integers|zero}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:87 (Number)}}\n[[Category:Integers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n  {{refimprove |date=April  2016}}\n  {{example farm |date=March 2010}}\n}}\n{{Infobox number\n| number = 87\n| divisor = 1, 3, 29, 87\n\n}}\n'''87''' ('''eighty-seven''') is the [[natural number]] following [[86 (number)|86]] and preceding [[88 (number)|88]].\n\n==In mathematics==\n'''87''' is:\n\n* the sum of the squares of the first four primes (87 = 2<sup>2</sup> + 3<sup>2</sup> + 5<sup>2</sup> + 7<sup>2</sup>).\n* the sum of the sums of the divisors of the first 10 [[positive integers]].<ref>{{Cite OEIS|1=A024916|2=sum_{k=1..n} sigma(k) where sigma(n) = sum of divisors of n}}</ref>\n* the twenty-sixth distinct [[semiprime]] and the eighth of the form (3.q).\n* 5! - 4! - 3! - 2! - 1! = 87\n\n==In sports==\n* [[Cricket]] [[Cricket in Australia|in Australia]] holds 87 as a superstitiously unlucky score and is referred to as \"the devil's number.\" This originates from the fact that 87 is [[13 (number)|13]] runs short of a [[Century (cricket)|century]]. 187, 287 and so on are also considered unlucky but is not as common as 87 on its own. \n* In the [[National Hockey League]], [[Wayne Gretzky]] scored a league-high 87 goals with the [[Edmonton Oilers]] in the [[1983\u201384 NHL season]].\n\n==In other fields==\n'''Eighty-seven''' is also:\n\n*The [[atomic number]] of [[francium]]\n*An answer to a popular puzzle question states 16, 06, 68, 88, xx, 98. The answer is 87 when looked upside down.\n*The number of years between the signing of the [[U.S. Declaration of Independence]] and the [[Battle of Gettysburg]], immortalized in [[Abraham Lincoln]]'s [[Gettysburg Address]] with the phrase \"''[[Eighty|fourscore]]'' and seven years ago...\"\n*The model number of [[Junkers Ju 87]]\n*The number of the French department [[Haute-Vienne]]\n*The [[code for international direct dial]] phone calls to [[Inmarsat]] and other services\n*The 87 [[filter (photography)|photographic filter]] blocks visible light allowing only infrared light to pass\n*The [[ISBN]] Group Identifier for books published in Denmark.\n*The opus number of the [[24 Preludes and Fugues (Shostakovich)|24 Preludes and Fugues]] of [[Dmitri Shostakovich]].\n*In [[model railroading]], the ratio of the popular [[H0 scale]] is 1:87. [[Proto:87]] scale claims to offer precise proportions of wheels and tracks of real railroads.\n*[[David Bowie]] CD (1987) ''[[Never Let Me Down]]'' includes the song, \"[['87 and Cry]]\"\n*The [[87th United States Congress]] met from January 3, 1961 - January 3, 1963, during John F. Kennedy's time in office\n*[[Ed McBain]]'s ''[[87th Precinct]]: Lightning'' film starred [[Randy Quaid]] (1995)\n*87 punch includes one bottle of [[Bacardi]] rum (eight years aged) and [[7-up]] (two-liter bottle)\n*[[Wenger]] [[Swiss Army Knife]] version XXL, listed in the ''[[Guinness Book of World Records]]'' as the world's most multi-functional [[penknife]] with 87 tools\n*''[[Sonnet 87]]'' by [[William Shakespeare]]\n*Vault 87 is a main location in the game ''[[Fallout 3]]''\n*[[M87*]] is the first black hole ever photographed.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of highways numbered 87]]\n{{Integers|zero}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:87 (Number)}}\n[[Category:Integers]]\n", "name_user": "129.205.113.156", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(87b Ogoja Rd Obudu Cross river state.)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/87_(number)"}
{"title_page": "Zarechny, Amur Oblast", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Zarechny\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0417\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0447\u043d\u044b\u0439\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Settlement\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Amur Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Amur Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Blagoveshchensky District, Amur Oblast|Blagoveshchensky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +9:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|50|14|N|127|40|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/amurskaya-oblast/blagoveschenskiy-rayon/zarechniy-poselok/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0435\u043b\u043a\u0430 \u0417\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0447\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0432 \u0410\u043c\u0443\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Zarechny''' ({{lang-ru|\u0417\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0447\u043d\u044b\u0439}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a settlement) in Grodekovsky Selsoviet of [[Blagoveshchensky District, Amur Oblast|Blagoveshchensky District]], [[Amur Oblast]], Russia. The population was 151 as of 2018.<ref>[http://amurstat.gks.ru/wps/wcm/connect/rosstat_ts/amurstat/resources/d600c10043769f3eb9effbdd898fc419/07_1_4.htm \u041e\u0446\u0435\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u0447\u0438\u0441\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0410\u043c\u0443\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u043f\u043e \u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430\u043c \u0438 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043c]</ref> There are 8 streets.\n\n== Geography ==\nThe village is located 5 km from the left bank of the Amur River, 8 km from Blagoveshchensk and 18 km from Grodekovo.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Blagoveshchensky District, Amur Oblast}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Amur Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Blagoveshchensky District, Amur Oblast]]\n\n{{AmurOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Zarechny\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0417\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0447\u043d\u044b\u0439\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Settlement\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Amur Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Amur Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Blagoveshchensky District, Amur Oblast|Blagoveshchensky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +9:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_