 health authority.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/olomouc/zpravy/koronavirus-unicov-litovel-cervenka.A200316_062222_olomouc-zpravy_jadv|title=Hygienici zav\u0159eli Litovel, Uni\u010dov a 19 obc\u00ed. V izolaci je 24 tis\u00edc lid\u00ed|date=16 March 2020|website=iDNES.cz}}</ref>\n|-\n| Quarantine of municipality of '''[[Kynice]]''', where a number of people were infected during the local volunteer fire department's ball.\n\nThe municipality has a population of 95.\n| 16 March 2020\n| From 16 March onwards (indefinitely).\n\n'''Lifted on 1 April 2020'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.irozhlas.cz/zpravy-domov/kynice-izolace-konec-karanteny-koronavirus-hasici-dezinfekce_2004011116_tzr |title=Kynice opou\u0161t\u00ed po dvou t\u00fddnech karant\u00e9nu. V izolaci z\u016fst\u00e1vaj\u00ed pouze nemocn\u00ed, hasi\u010di \u010d\u00e1sti obce dezinfikuj\u00ed &#124; iROZHLAS - spolehliv\u00e9 zpr\u00e1vy |publisher=Irozhlas.cz |date=2020-04-01 |accessdate=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n| Same conditions as in other quaranteened areas.\n| Local health authority.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.novinky.cz/zahranicni/koronavirus/clanek/hygienici-zcela-uzavreli-kynici-kde-se-virus-rozsiril-na-hasicske-zabave-40316848|title=Hygienici zcela uzav\u0159eli Kynice, kde se virus roz\u0161\u00ed\u0159il na hasi\u010dsk\u00e9 z\u00e1bav\u011b - Novinky.cz|website=www.novinky.cz}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=7 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Social distancing measures'''\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Public authorities' activity reduction'''\n| 12 March 2020\n| 14 March to 1 April.\n\nExtended until 11 April.\n\nExtended until 19 April.\n| '''Public authorities restricted to perform only to necessary duties.'''\n\nRestrictions on duties requiring personal contact with the public. Restriction of office hours to 3 hours on Monday and Wednesday. Only the lowest possible number of employees to be present when necessary. Duty to implement rotations of employees in a way that prevents contact between selected groups.\n\n'''Partially revoked on 6 April 2020''': {{Interlanguage link|Czechpoint|cs|Czech POINT}} resumes service.\n| Government Resolution No. 194/2000 (until 24 March)\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12745/2020-3/MIN/KAN (from 24 March onwards)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40684&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20prodlou%C5%BEen%C3%AD%20omezen%C3%AD%20%C4%8Dinnosti%20OVM%20a%20SO.pdf |title=Info |publisher=www.mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12745/2020-5/MIN/KAN (from 1 April onwards)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40760&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20prodlou%C5%BEen%C3%AD%20na%C5%99%C3%ADzen%C3%AD%20omezen%C3%A9ho%20provozu%20OVM%20a%20SO.pdf |title=Info |publisher=www.mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 15190/2020-2/MIN/KAN (Czechpoint reopening)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40880&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Ukon%C4%8Den%C3%AD%20mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9ho%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20ze%20dne%2030.%203.%202020%20ke%20kontaktn%C3%ADm%20m%C3%ADst%C5%AFm%20ve%C5%99ejn%C3%A9%20spr%C3%A1vy%20Czech%20POINT.pdf |title=Info |publisher=www.mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 15757/2020-4/MIN/KAN<ref>https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40915&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20na%C5%99%C3%ADzen%C3%AD%20spr%C3%A1vn%C3%ADm%20%C3%BA%C5%99ad%C5%AFm%20II..pdf</ref>\n|-\n| 9 April 2020\n| From 20 April onwards (indefinitely)\n| '''Public authorities open with special measures'''\n\nPublic authorities instructed to prioritize email or telephone communication over physical meetings. \n\nOpening hours back to normal. Personal meetings either through barier or if possible with 2 meters distance. Obligation to ensure distance of 2 meters in hallways, waiting rooms, etc. Obligation to set up hand sanitizers in hallways. Obligation to frequently desinfect surfaces incl. doorhandles, elevator buttons, etc.\n\nDuty to implement rotations of employees in a way that prevents contact between selected groups. Duty to priritize work from home where possible.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 15757/2020-3/MIN/KAN<ref>https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40914&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20na%C5%99%C3%ADzen%C3%AD%20spr%C3%A1vn%C3%ADm%20%C3%BA%C5%99ad%C5%AFm%20I..pdf</ref>\n|-\n| {{No|'''Obligatory face cover''' (respirator or similar)}}\n| 18 March 2020\n| From 19 March until 30 March\n\nFrom 30 March onwards (indefinitely)\n| Ban on movement outside of the home without having mouth and nose covered by a respirator, face mask or similar.\n\nExemptions from 30 March onwards:\n* car drivers, if they are alone within a closed vehicle,\n* children younger than 2 years.\n\nScope of exemptions widened on 7 April:\n* conducting sports in accordance with curfew exemptions (incl. walking/running in parks and nature)\n\nScope of Exemptions widened on 9 April:\n* drivers of public transportation if they are alone within a confined space\n* people with severe autistic disorder\n* people within a closed vehicle, if all of them are members of the same household\n| Government resolution No. 247 (published as No. 106/2020 Coll.) (until 30 March)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c8/Sb0041-2020.pdf |title=Data |publisher=upload.wikimedia.org |date= |accessdate=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 13894/2020-1/MIN/KAN (after 30 March)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40763&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3